        >
          SEIU Local 1107
        </div>
        <h1
          class="shadowClass uppercase font-bold font-Roboto text-supernova-400 text-center text-7xl lg:text-9xl mt-4 lg:mt-2"
        >
          Lobby Day 2025
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <div
    class="max-w-[85vw] md:max-w-screen-sm m-auto flex flex-col xl:flex-row justify-center"
  >
    <Image
      src={CareAgenda1}
      alt=""
      class="lg:mx-1 my-1 rounded-sm shadow-md shadow-black"
    />
    <Image
      src={CareAgenda2}
      alt=""
      class="lg:mx-1 my-1 rounded-sm shadow-md shadow-black"
    />
  </div>
  <HeadingTitle text="Our 2025 Priorities" />
  <div
    class="m-auto flex flex-col lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-2 max-w-[90vw] md:max-w-screen-md lg:max-w-screen-lg xl:max-w-screen-xl"
  >
    <div class="py-1.5">
      <span class="text-xl font-bold"
        ><LinkText
          href="https://www.leg.state.nv.us/App/NELIS/REL/83rd2025/Bill/11877/Text"
          target="_blank">Assembly Bill 68 (AB 68)</LinkText
        > Positive Credit for Rent</span
      >
      <ul class="pt-1 list-disc pl-4">
        <li>
          Would allow renters to opt-in to positive credit reporting every time
          they pay rent on time.
        </li>
        <li>
          This would help the nearly half a million Nevadans who are not
          currently receiving credit for paying their rent and build their
          credit.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Update:</b> AB 68 did not pass Friday's committee deadline; however,
          it is going to be amended into another housing bill.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="py-1.5">
      <span class="text-xl font-bold"
        ><LinkText
          href="https://www.leg.state.nv.us/App/NELIS/REL/83rd2025/Bill/12200/Text"
          target="_blank">Senate Bill 182 (SB 182)</LinkText
        > Healthcare Staffing Ratios</span
      >
      <ul class="pt-1 list-disc pl-4">
        <li>
          Would place safe patient to staff ratios into law to ensure safe
          working conditions and better outcomes for hospital patients.
        </li>
        <li>SB 182 will save money, save jobs, and save lives.</li>
        <li>
          <b>Update:</b> SB 182 passed out of the Senate Health & Human Services
          on a party line vote of 3-2 with Democratic Senators Doñate, Lange, and
          Taylor voting yes, and Republican Senators Titus and Stone voting no.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Update:</b> SB 182 is likely onto the Senate Finance committee to review
          the fiscal impact of the bill before being voted on by the entirety of
          the State Senate.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="py-1.5">
      <span class="text-xl font-bold"
        ><LinkText
          href="https://www.leg.state.nv.us/App/NELIS/REL/83rd2025/Bill/12201/Text"
          target="_blank">Senate Bill 183 (SB 183)</LinkText
        > Child and Family Case Worker Ratios</span
      >
      <ul class="pt-1 list-disc pl-4">
        <li>
          Will establish a ratio for the maximum number of children a case
          worker may have assigned to them at 30 children to 1 case worker.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Update:</b> SB 183 passed out of the Senate Health & Human Services
          Committee unanimously.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Next Steps:</b> SB 183 is sent to the Senate Floor to be voted on by
          the entire State Senate. This must be done by April 22nd.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="py-1.5">
      <span class="text-xl font-bold"
        ><LinkText
          href="https://www.leg.state.nv.us/App/NELIS/REL/83rd2025/Bill/12528/Text"
          target="_blank">Senate Bill 306 (SB 306)</LinkText
        > No Eject. No Reject.</span
      >
      <ul class="pt-1 list-disc pl-4">
        <li>
          Requires the State of Nevada to place children in proper mental health
          facilities rather than temporary shelters like Child Haven.
        </li>
        <li>
          Requires any child that is being transferred out of a facility to have
          a discharge plan with certain requirements.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Update:</b> SB 306 passed out of the Senate Health & Human Services
          Committee unanimously.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Next Steps:</b> SB 306 is sent to the Senate Floor to be voted on by
          the entire State Senate. This must be done by April 22nd.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col my-4 m-auto">
    <HeadingTitle text="Other Bills We're Tracking" />
    <div
      class="h-[60vh] py-4 overflow-y-auto max-w-[95vw] lg:max-w-screen-lg xl:max-w-screen-xl m-auto bg-white shadow-md shadow-black p-4"
